- end field 08780f37-3645-4582-a36a-69bdd1297122 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item cf1d64b5-54c5-47b0-b881-e76398726969 --><!-- begin field 5aefc16c-d57e-4dea-8129-605422a3d1fd --><ul><li>The recommendations on when to suspect obstructive sleep apnoea (OSAS) in adults are largely based on the Scottish Intercollegiate Guidelines Network guideline <em>Management of obstructive sleep apnoea/hypopnoea syndrome (OSAHS) in adults </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/obstructive-sleep-apnoea-syndrome/references/\">SIGN, 2003</a>].</li><li>The recommendations on when to suspect OSAS in children are largely based on expert opinion in a clinical review in the British Medical Journal, <em>Paediatric obstructive sleep apnoea </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/obstructive-sleep-apnoea-syndrome/references/\">Powell et al, 2010</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 5aefc16c-d57e-4dea-8129-605422a3d1fd --><!-- end item cf1d64b5-54c5-47b0-b881-e76398726969 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}